-- Ex-UBS Client Zaltsberg Admits Hiding $2.6 Million From IRS in Switzerland
-- David Voreacos
-- 2010-07-01T15:17:54Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-07-01/ex-ubs-client-zaltsberg-admits-hiding-2-6-million-from-irs-in-switzerland.html

          
          
             Leonid Zaltsberg, a former UBS AG
client, pleaded guilty to filing a false tax return that failed
to disclose a Swiss bank account holding $2.6 million.  
 Zaltsberg, 75, entered his guilty plea today in federal
court in Newark, New Jersey.  
 To contact the reporter on this story:
